# Music Room Project Structure

This is a React Native project built with Expo and Supabase. The main app code is located in the `react/` directory.

## Key Directories

- **`react/app/`** - Expo Router pages with route groups

  - `(auth)/` - Authentication routes (login, register, etc.)
  - `(main)/` - Main app routes (home, profile, etc.)
  - `_layout.tsx` - Root layout configuration

- **`react/components/`** - UI components

  - `ui/` - Gluestack UI components (buttons, providers, etc.)

- **`react/contexts/`** - React Context providers

  - `authCtx.tsx` - Authentication context

- **`react/config/`** - Configuration files

  - `supabase.ts` - Supabase client configuration

- **`react/hooks/`** - Custom React hooks

  - `useStorageState.tsx` - Storage state management

- \*\*`react/assets/` - Images and static files

## File Naming Conventions

- Use descriptive names for route files (e.g., `home.tsx` instead of `index.tsx`)
- Group related routes in parentheses like `(auth)/` and `(main)/`
- Keep components in the `components/` directory
- Store utilities and configs in `config/` and `hooks/` directories
